Kubernetes -> Controller: enqueue OpaInstance reconcile
Controller -> BaseReconciler: Reconcile(request)
BaseReconciler -> ServiceManager: reconcile desired OpaInstance
group Lookup and bind
alt tracked or explicit OCI identity already exists
ServiceManager -> OCI: GetOpaInstance
else tracked identity is missing
ServiceManager -> OCI: ListOpaInstances(filters:\ncompartmentId, displayName)
alt reusable OCI resource is not found
ServiceManager -> OCI: CreateOpaInstance
loop create pending CREATING
ServiceManager -> OCI: GetOpaInstance
end
else reusable OCI resource already exists
ServiceManager -> OCI: GetOpaInstance
end
ServiceManager --> BaseReconciler: persist resolved OCI identity in status
end
alt delete requested
group Delete
ServiceManager -> OCI: DeleteOpaInstance
ServiceManager -> OCI: confirm delete via GetOpaInstance or\nListOpaInstances
loop delete pending DELETING
ServiceManager -> OCI: GetOpaInstance or ListOpaInstances
end
alt cleanup or finalizer release is blocked
ServiceManager --> BaseReconciler: retain delete state and retry
else delete completion observed
ServiceManager --> BaseReconciler: release finalizer after delete completion
end
end
else OCI state is retryable
ServiceManager --> BaseReconciler: requeue while OCI remains in\nCREATING, UPDATING, DELETING
else live state requires field-aware\ndrift evaluation
group Drift handling
note over ServiceManager,OCI
Supported update surface: definedTags,
description, displayName, freeformTags
Reject before mutate: force-new fields
compartmentId, consumptionModel, idcsAt,
isBreakglassEnabled (+2 more)
Lookup filters: compartmentId,
displayName
Lookup matching: exact compartmentId
plus displayName unique match in ACTIVE,
CREATING, UPDATING, or INACTIVE;
duplicate matches fail
end note
opt force-new or conflicting drift is detected
ServiceManager --> BaseReconciler: reject before OCI mutation
end
opt supported mutable drift is detected
ServiceManager -> OCI: Apply UpdateOpaInstance only for\nmutable fields definedTags,\ndescription, displayName,\nfreeformTags
loop update pending UPDATING
ServiceManager -> OCI: GetOpaInstance
end
end
ServiceManager -> OCI: run helper hooks\ncreate=tfresource.CreateResource,\ntfresource.WaitForWorkRequestWithErrorHandling\nentity=opainstance action=CREATED;\nupdate=tfresource.UpdateResource,\ntfresource.WaitForWorkRequestWithErrorHandling\nentity=opainstance action=UPDATED;\ndelete=tfresource.DeleteResource,\ntfresource.WaitForWorkRequestWithErrorHandling\nentity=opainstance action=DELETED
ServiceManager -> OCI: apply follow-up strategy\ncreate=GetWorkRequest ->\nGetOpaInstance;\nupdate=GetWorkRequest ->\nGetOpaInstance;\ndelete=GetWorkRequest ->\nGetOpaInstance/ListOpaInstances\nconfirm-delete
end
ServiceManager --> BaseReconciler: status=required,\nfinalizer=retain-until-confirmed-delete
end
BaseReconciler --> Controller: requeue on provisioning, updating,\nterminating
note right of ServiceManager
shared diagram:
shared/diagrams/shared-resolution-sequence.svg
shared delete diagram:
shared/diagrams/shared-delete-sequence.svg
Start from the shared resolution sequence for
OCID binding, datasource pagination, and
create-or-update dispatch.
Layer the shared delete sequence when finalizer
retention, delete confirmation, work-request
polling, or Secret cleanup apply.
archetype batch: Generated service-manager
controllers follow the shared resolution and
delete sequences with imported waits and
controller-local policy.
service: opa
slug: opainstance
kind: OpaInstance
archetype: generated-service-manager
status/finalizer: required /
retain-until-confirmed-delete
requeue: provisioning, updating, terminating
provider states: create CREATING; update
UPDATING; delete DELETING
follow-up: create=GetWorkRequest ->
GetOpaInstance; update=GetWorkRequest ->
GetOpaInstance; delete=GetWorkRequest ->
GetOpaInstance/ListOpaInstances confirm-delete
supported drift: definedTags, description,
displayName, freeformTags
reject before mutate: force-new fields
compartmentId, consumptionModel, idcsAt,
isBreakglassEnabled (+2 more)
create-only fields: none
list lookup: oci_opa_opa_instances filters
compartmentId, displayName; exact compartmentId
plus displayName unique match in ACTIVE,
CREATING, UPDATING, or INACTIVE; duplicate
matches fail
conflicts: none
open gaps: none
Reviewed lifecycle mapping treats CREATING as
provisioning, UPDATING as updating, ACTIVE and
INACTIVE as success, and DELETING as
terminating; FAILED is terminal and DELETED is
only a delete-confirmation target.
Create, update, and delete responses expose
work-request headers but do not return an
OpaInstance body. The runtime resumes through
GetWorkRequest, recovers the affected
OpaInstance OCID from work-request resources,
and rereads GetOpaInstance before settling.
Pre-create reuse only runs when both
spec.compartmentId and spec.displayName are
present and keeps exact compartmentId plus
displayName matching bounded to ACTIVE,
CREATING, UPDATING, or INACTIVE summaries.
Only displayName, description, freeformTags, and
definedTags reconcile in place; IdcsAt is
create-time-only and normalized out of
post-create parity because OCI does not echo it,
while compartmentId, shapeName,
consumptionModel, meteringType, and
isBreakglassEnabled remain replacement-only.
ChangeOpaInstanceCompartment, StartOpaInstance,
and StopOpaInstance remain out of scope for the
published runtime surface. Delete keeps the
finalizer until the work request is terminal and
GetOpaInstance or fallback ListOpaInstances
confirms the resource is gone.
end note
